/*
==============================================================================
  OID4VCI Final 1.0
  Deferred-Issuance Holder-Key Substitution — Tamarin Prover Model
==============================================================================

  Tool:            Tamarin Prover (>= 1.10.0)
  Spec analysed:   OpenID for Verifiable Credential Issuance 1.0 (FINAL)
                   T. Lodderstedt, K. Yasuda, T. Looker, P. Bastian
                   16 September 2025

  Companion:       Security & Trust in the OpenID4VC Ecosystem (Mar 2024)
                   D. Fett, T. Lodderstedt
                   §6.2 (P-10), §6.7 (P-50)


==============================================================================
  FOUR CONFIGURATIONS — pass exactly one -D flag at runtime
==============================================================================

  -DVULNERABLE  spec-as-written
  -DFIXED       v1 fix (tx-id binding signature) — closes C2, scoped P-10
  -DFIXED_V2    v2 attempt (keyProof signs over h(pkB)) — DOES NOT close C2'
                  Retained as a NEGATIVE RESULT in the paper: shows that
                  augmenting the keyProof payload cannot close C2' because
                  the adversary already holds the holder signing key.
  -DFIXED_V3    v3 fix (v1 + AT-bound pkH, RFC 7800 cnf style)
                  - Wallet generates skH/pkH BEFORE requesting AT
                  - AT carries pkH as a confirmation method
                  - Issuer verifies that the keyProof's pkH equals the
                    AT-bound pkH
                  Closes both C2 and C2'; P-10 verifies WITHOUT scoping.


==============================================================================
  THE DEFERRED-ISSUANCE HOLDER-KEY SUBSTITUTION ATTACK* (recap)

  (* This attack name will be referred as -C2-)
==============================================================================

  Final 1.0 §9.2 line 710: the credential_response_encryption MAY differ
  from the original Credential Request and the Issuer MUST use the new one.
  An attacker holding (tid, AT, skDPoP) can submit a deferred request with
  their own response-encryption key and decrypt the issued credential.
  P-50 holds (cred bound to honest pkH); P-10 broken.


==============================================================================
  THE C2' RESIDUAL (recap)
==============================================================================

  Even with v1's tx-id binding signature, the wallet's pkB sits inside the
  JWE-encrypted Credential Request unauthenticated to the wallet's identity.
  An adversary holding (AT_A, skDPoP_A) from wallet A AND skH_B from a
  separate wallet B can construct a credential request pairing pkH_B with
  an adversary-chosen pkB_adv, then complete the deferred flow with their
  own bind signature. The credential is bound to pkH_B (an already-
  compromised identity) but issued under A's authorization. This is a
  fresh-issuance authorization break, not a credential-confidentiality
  break of an honest wallet, but it has security implications including
  rate-limit bypass and post-compromise PII re-issuance.


==============================================================================
  WHY v2 DID NOT WORK — recorded for the paper's negative-result subsection
==============================================================================

  v2 attempted to bind pkB into the keyProof payload:
       keyProofPayloadV2 = <'openid4vci-proof+jwt-v2', 'ES256',
                            pkH, h(pkB), CI, iat>
  Tamarin falsified both c2prime_attack_blocked_v2 and the unscoped
  P10_credential_secrecy_fixed_v2. The reason is structural: C2' presumes
  adversary possession of the holder signing key skH_B, so any signature
  constructible by the wallet (over any payload, with any embedded fields)
  is also constructible by the adversary. No augmentation of the keyProof
  payload can close C2' under this threat model. The fix must come from
  outside the wallet's signing-key space.


==============================================================================
  PROPOSED FIX v3 — AT-bound holder key (RFC 7800 cnf-style)
==============================================================================

  The Authorization Server learns the wallet's holder public key pkH at
  the token-request stage (alongside the DPoP key pkDPoP) and embeds it
  in the issued Access Token as a confirmation method. The AT shape
  becomes:
       AT = aToken(~atSecret, pkDPoP, pkH, CI, AS)
  where pkH is the wallet's intended holder key for the credential.

  At the Credential Endpoint, the Credential Issuer extracts pkH from the
  AT and verifies that the keyProof's pkH equals this AT-bound pkH. An
  adversary submitting a credential request under leaked (AT_A, skDPoP_A)
  is forced to use pkH_A. To produce a keyProof signed over (pkH_A, ...)
  they need skH_A — which (under NoHolderKeyLeak(A)) they do not have.
  C2' is structurally closed.

  Suggested IETF spec text v3:
     "The Token Endpoint MUST accept a `cnf` parameter binding the
      Access Token to the wallet's holder public key. The Authorization
      Server MUST embed this `cnf` claim in the issued Access Token.
      The Credential Issuer MUST verify that the `pkH` extracted from
      the keyProof matches the `cnf` claim of the presented AT."


==============================================================================
  ABSTRACTIONS — unchanged from v1/v2
==============================================================================

  A1. AS flow: replaced by Wallet_Get_AT. In v3 this rule additionally
      generates skH/pkH and embeds pkH in the AT.
  A2. Metadata: pkR_CI via !CI_ReqEncPk.
  A3. TLS: replaced by In/Out (over-approximation).
  A4. Wallet attestation, replay defences: not relevant to C2/C2'.
  A5. Credential format: single signature over (CI, pkH, 'PII-dataset').


==============================================================================
  EXPECTED VERDICTS
==============================================================================

  -DVULNERABLE     c2_attack_witness                 verified
                   P10_credential_secrecy_vuln       falsified

  -DFIXED   (v1)   c2prime_attack_witness_fixed      verified
                   P10_credential_secrecy_fixed      verified (scoped)

  -DFIXED_V2 (v2)  c2prime_attack_blocked_v2         falsified  ★ negative
                   P10_credential_secrecy_fixed_v2   falsified  ★ result ★

  -DFIXED_V3 (v3)  c2prime_attack_blocked_v3         verified  ★ closes C2'
                   P10_credential_secrecy_fixed_v3   verified  ★ unscoped


==============================================================================
  HOW TO RUN
==============================================================================

  tamarin-prover --prove -DVULNERABLE --auto-sources OID4VCI_C2_v3.spthy ...
  tamarin-prover --prove -DFIXED      --auto-sources OID4VCI_C2_v3.spthy ...
  tamarin-prover --prove -DFIXED_V2   --auto-sources OID4VCI_C2_v3.spthy ...
  tamarin-prover --prove -DFIXED_V3   --auto-sources OID4VCI_C2_v3.spthy ...


==============================================================================
*/

theory OID4VCI_C2 begin

builtins: signing, hashing


/*
============================================================================
  PROBABILISTIC PUBLIC-KEY ENCRYPTION (JWE)
============================================================================
*/
functions:    penc/3, pdec/2
equations:    pdec(penc(m, pk(k), r), k) = m


/*
============================================================================
  OPAQUE ACCESS TOKENS
============================================================================
  v1/v2: aToken/4   = aToken(~atSecret, pkDPoP, CI, AS)
  v3:    aTokenV3/5 = aTokenV3(~atSecret, pkDPoP, pkH, CI, AS)
                                                 ^^^^ cnf-bound holder key
  Both private; adversary cannot construct without an explicit Reveal.
  Two distinct functions so the FIXED/FIXED_V2 branches keep their
  4-argument AT shape unchanged.
*/
functions:    aToken/4   [private]
functions:    aTokenV3/5 [private]


// ============================================================================
//                                MACROS
// ============================================================================

macros:

  // -------- DPoP proof (RFC 9449), audience-tagged --------
  dpopPayloadCred(CI, pkDPoP, jti, AT)
        = <'dpop+jwt', CI, 'POST', 'credential', pkDPoP, jti, AT>,
  dpopPayloadDef(CI, pkDPoP, jti, AT)
        = <'dpop+jwt', CI, 'POST', 'deferred',   pkDPoP, jti, AT>,
  dpopProofCred(CI, pkDPoP, jti, AT, skDPoP)
        = sign(dpopPayloadCred(CI, pkDPoP, jti, AT), skDPoP),
  dpopProofDef(CI, pkDPoP, jti, AT, skDPoP)
        = sign(dpopPayloadDef(CI, pkDPoP, jti, AT), skDPoP),

  // -------- Key Proof JWT v1 (used by VULNERABLE, FIXED, FIXED_V3) --------
  keyProofPayload(CI, pkH, iat)
        = <'openid4vci-proof+jwt', 'ES256', pkH, CI, iat>,
  keyProofJWT(CI, pkH, iat, skH)
        = sign(keyProofPayload(CI, pkH, iat), skH),

  // -------- Key Proof JWT v2 (used by FIXED_V2 only) --------
  // Negative-result fix attempt; does NOT close C2'.
  keyProofPayloadV2(CI, pkH, pkB, iat)
        = <'openid4vci-proof+jwt-v2', 'ES256', pkH, h(pkB), CI, iat>,
  keyProofJWTV2(CI, pkH, pkB, iat, skH)
        = sign(keyProofPayloadV2(CI, pkH, pkB, iat), skH),

  // -------- Issued credential --------
  credPayload(CI, pkH)
        = <'credential', CI, 'PII-dataset', pkH>,
  credentialSig(CI, pkH, ltkCI)
        = sign(credPayload(CI, pkH), ltkCI),

  // -------- Tx-Id binding signature (FIXED, FIXED_V2, FIXED_V3) --------
  txIdBindPayload(CI, tid, pkE_new)
        = <'oid4vci-tid-bind', CI, tid, h(pkE_new)>,
  txIdBindSig(CI, tid, pkE_new, skB)
        = sign(txIdBindPayload(CI, tid, pkE_new), skB)


// ============================================================================
//                              PREDICATES
// ============================================================================

predicates:
  HonestCI(CI)            <=> not (Ex #r. Reveal_CI(CI) @ r),
  HonestCIReqEnc(CI)      <=> not (Ex #r. Reveal_CI_ReqEncKey(CI) @ r),
  NoHolderKeyLeak(Wid)    <=> not (Ex p #r. Reveal_HolderKey(Wid, p) @ r),
  NoEncKeyLeak(Wid)       <=> not (Ex p #r. Reveal_WalletEncKey(Wid, p) @ r),
  NoBindKeyLeak(Wid)      <=> not (Ex p #r. Reveal_WalletBindKey(Wid, p) @ r),
  NoStoredATLeak(Wid, CI) <=> not (Ex at #r. Reveal_StoredAT(Wid, CI, at) @ r),
  NoDPoPKeyLeak(Wid)      <=> not (Ex p #r. Reveal_DPoPKey(Wid, p) @ r),
  NoTxIdLeak(Wid, CI)     <=> not (Ex t #r. Reveal_TxId(Wid, CI, t) @ r)


// ============================================================================
//                              RESTRICTIONS
// ============================================================================

restriction Eq:
  "All x y #i. Eq(x,y) @ i ==> x = y"

restriction OnlyOnceV:
  "All x #i #j. OnlyOnceV(x) @ i & OnlyOnceV(x) @ j ==> #i = #j"

restriction UniqueCIKey:
  "All CI k1 k2 #i #j.
      CIKey(CI,k1) @ i & CIKey(CI,k2) @ j ==> k1 = k2"

restriction UniqueCIReqEncKey:
  "All CI k1 k2 #i #j.
      CIReqEncSk(CI,k1) @ i & CIReqEncSk(CI,k2) @ j ==> k1 = k2"


// ============================================================================
//                            PARTY SETUP
// ============================================================================

rule Register_CI [color=#fef3c7, role="Setup"]:
    [ Fr(~ltkCI) ]
  --[ Register_CI($CI),
      CIKey($CI, ~ltkCI),
      OnlyOnceV(<'register-ci', $CI>) ]->
    [ !Ltk_CI($CI, ~ltkCI),
      Out(pk(~ltkCI)) ]

rule CI_Publish_RequestEncKey [color=#fef3c7, role="Setup"]:
    [ Fr(~skR_CI),
      !Ltk_CI($CI, ~ltkCI) ]
  --[ CIRequestEncKey($CI, pk(~skR_CI)),
      CIReqEncSk($CI, ~skR_CI),
      OnlyOnceV(<'ci-req-enc', $CI>) ]->
    [ !CI_ReqEncSk($CI, ~skR_CI),
      !CI_ReqEncPk($CI, pk(~skR_CI)),
      Out(pk(~skR_CI)) ]


// ============================================================================
//             ABSTRACTED AS FLOW (Wallet_Get_AT)
// ============================================================================

#ifdef VULNERABLE
rule Wallet_Get_AT [color=#fef9c3, role="Wallet"]:
  let
    pkDPoP = pk(~skDPoP)
    AT     = aToken(~atSecret, pkDPoP, $CI, $AS)
  in
    [ Fr(~sid), Fr(~skDPoP), Fr(~atSecret) ]
  --[ Wallet_Got_AT($Wid, $CI, ~sid, AT),
      ATIssued($AS, $CI, $Wid, AT, pkDPoP) ]->
    [ W_HasAT($Wid, $CI, $AS, ~sid, AT, ~skDPoP, pkDPoP),
      !Valid_AT($CI, AT, $AS, $Wid, pkDPoP),
      !StoredDPoPKey($Wid, ~skDPoP, pkDPoP),
      !StoredAT($Wid, $CI, AT) ]
#endif

#ifdef FIXED
rule Wallet_Get_AT [color=#fef9c3, role="Wallet"]:
  let
    pkDPoP = pk(~skDPoP)
    AT     = aToken(~atSecret, pkDPoP, $CI, $AS)
  in
    [ Fr(~sid), Fr(~skDPoP), Fr(~atSecret) ]
  --[ Wallet_Got_AT($Wid, $CI, ~sid, AT),
      ATIssued($AS, $CI, $Wid, AT, pkDPoP) ]->
    [ W_HasAT($Wid, $CI, $AS, ~sid, AT, ~skDPoP, pkDPoP),
      !Valid_AT($CI, AT, $AS, $Wid, pkDPoP),
      !StoredDPoPKey($Wid, ~skDPoP, pkDPoP),
      !StoredAT($Wid, $CI, AT) ]
#endif

#ifdef FIXED_V2
rule Wallet_Get_AT [color=#fef9c3, role="Wallet"]:
  let
    pkDPoP = pk(~skDPoP)
    AT     = aToken(~atSecret, pkDPoP, $CI, $AS)
  in
    [ Fr(~sid), Fr(~skDPoP), Fr(~atSecret) ]
  --[ Wallet_Got_AT($Wid, $CI, ~sid, AT),
      ATIssued($AS, $CI, $Wid, AT, pkDPoP) ]->
    [ W_HasAT($Wid, $CI, $AS, ~sid, AT, ~skDPoP, pkDPoP),
      !Valid_AT($CI, AT, $AS, $Wid, pkDPoP),
      !StoredDPoPKey($Wid, ~skDPoP, pkDPoP),
      !StoredAT($Wid, $CI, AT) ]
#endif

// ★ V3: AT carries pkH as a confirmation-method binding.
// The wallet generates skH/pkH at AT-acquisition time. The AS embeds
// pkH in the AT structure (aTokenV3/5). The Issuer can later extract
// pkH from the AT and verify it matches the keyProof's pkH.
#ifdef FIXED_V3
rule Wallet_Get_AT [color=#fef9c3, role="Wallet"]:
  let
    pkDPoP = pk(~skDPoP)
    pkH    = pk(~skH)
    AT     = aTokenV3(~atSecret, pkDPoP, pkH, $CI, $AS)   // ★ pkH bound ★
  in
    [ Fr(~sid), Fr(~skDPoP), Fr(~atSecret),
      Fr(~skH) ]                                          // ★ skH at AT time ★
  --[ Wallet_Got_AT($Wid, $CI, ~sid, AT),
      ATIssued($AS, $CI, $Wid, AT, pkDPoP),
      ATBoundToHolder($AS, $CI, $Wid, AT, pkH),           // ★ binding event ★
      WalletGen_HolderKey($Wid, ~sid, pkH),
      HolderKeyFresh($Wid, ~skH, pkH) ]->
    [ W_HasAT_V3($Wid, $CI, $AS, ~sid, AT,
                 ~skDPoP, pkDPoP,
                 ~skH, pkH),
      !Valid_AT_V3($CI, AT, $AS, $Wid, pkDPoP, pkH),
      !StoredDPoPKey($Wid, ~skDPoP, pkDPoP),
      !StoredAT($Wid, $CI, AT),
      !StoredHolderKey($Wid, ~skH, pkH) ]
#endif


// ============================================================================
//                            REVEAL RULES
// ============================================================================

rule Reveal_CI_Ltk [color=#fecaca, role="Adv"]:
    [ !Ltk_CI($CI, ~ltkCI) ] --[ Reveal_CI($CI) ]-> [ Out(~ltkCI) ]

rule Reveal_CI_ReqEncKey_Rule [color=#fecaca, role="Adv"]:
    [ !CI_ReqEncSk($CI, ~skR) ]
  --[ Reveal_CI_ReqEncKey($CI) ]->
    [ Out(~skR) ]

rule Reveal_HolderKey_Rule [color=#fecaca, role="Adv"]:
    [ !StoredHolderKey($Wid, ~skH, pkH) ]
  --[ Reveal_HolderKey($Wid, pkH) ]->
    [ Out(~skH) ]

rule Reveal_WalletEncKey_Rule [color=#fecaca, role="Adv"]:
    [ !StoredWalletEncKey($Wid, ~skE, pkE) ]
  --[ Reveal_WalletEncKey($Wid, pkE) ]->
    [ Out(~skE) ]

rule Reveal_DPoPKey_Rule [color=#fecaca, role="Adv"]:
    [ !StoredDPoPKey($Wid, ~skDPoP, pkDPoP) ]
  --[ Reveal_DPoPKey($Wid, pkDPoP) ]->
    [ Out(~skDPoP) ]

rule Reveal_StoredAT_Rule [color=#fecaca, role="Adv"]:
    [ !StoredAT($Wid, $CI, AT) ]
  --[ Reveal_StoredAT($Wid, $CI, AT) ]->
    [ Out(AT) ]

rule Reveal_TxId_Rule [color=#fecaca, role="Adv"]:
    [ !PendingTxId($Wid, $CI, tid) ]
  --[ Reveal_TxId($Wid, $CI, tid) ]->
    [ Out(tid) ]

#ifdef FIXED
rule Reveal_WalletBindKey_Rule [color=#fecaca, role="Adv"]:
    [ !StoredBindKey($Wid, ~skB, pkB) ]
  --[ Reveal_WalletBindKey($Wid, pkB) ]->
    [ Out(~skB) ]
#endif

#ifdef FIXED_V2
rule Reveal_WalletBindKey_Rule [color=#fecaca, role="Adv"]:
    [ !StoredBindKey($Wid, ~skB, pkB) ]
  --[ Reveal_WalletBindKey($Wid, pkB) ]->
    [ Out(~skB) ]
#endif

#ifdef FIXED_V3
rule Reveal_WalletBindKey_Rule [color=#fecaca, role="Adv"]:
    [ !StoredBindKey($Wid, ~skB, pkB) ]
  --[ Reveal_WalletBindKey($Wid, pkB) ]->
    [ Out(~skB) ]
#endif


// ============================================================================
//   CREDENTIAL REQUEST (Final §7.2)
// ============================================================================

#ifdef VULNERABLE
rule Wallet_Send_Credential_Req [color=#d1fae5, role="Wallet"]:
  let
    pkH      = pk(~skH)
    pkE_W    = pk(~skE_W)
    keyProof = keyProofJWT($CI, pkH, ~iat, ~skH)
    dpopPC   = dpopProofCred($CI, pkDPoP, ~jti_c, AT, ~skDPoP)
    inner    = <'credential-req', AT, dpopPC, pkH, keyProof,
                'crypt-resp', pkE_W>
    outer    = <'credential-req-jwe', penc(inner, pkR_CI, ~rEnc)>
  in
    [ W_HasAT($Wid, $CI, $AS, ~sid, AT, ~skDPoP, pkDPoP),
      !CI_ReqEncPk($CI, pkR_CI),
      Fr(~skH), Fr(~iat), Fr(~jti_c), Fr(~skE_W), Fr(~rEnc) ]
  --[ Wallet_Sent_Cred_Req($Wid, $CI, ~sid, pkH, AT),
      WalletGen_HolderKey($Wid, ~sid, pkH),
      WalletGen_EncKey($Wid, ~sid, pkE_W),
      HolderKeyFresh($Wid, ~skH, pkH),
      EncKeyFresh($Wid, ~skE_W, pkE_W) ]->
    [ W_AwaitingTxId($Wid, $CI, $AS, ~sid, AT,
                     ~skH, pkH, ~skE_W, pkE_W, ~skDPoP, pkDPoP),
      !StoredHolderKey($Wid, ~skH, pkH),
      !StoredWalletEncKey($Wid, ~skE_W, pkE_W),
      Out(outer) ]
#endif

#ifdef FIXED
rule Wallet_Send_Credential_Req [color=#d1fae5, role="Wallet"]:
  let
    pkH      = pk(~skH)
    pkE_W    = pk(~skE_W)
    pkB      = pk(~skB)
    keyProof = keyProofJWT($CI, pkH, ~iat, ~skH)
    dpopPC   = dpopProofCred($CI, pkDPoP, ~jti_c, AT, ~skDPoP)
    inner    = <'credential-req-fixed', AT, dpopPC, pkH, keyProof,
                'crypt-resp', pkE_W, 'tid-bind', pkB>
    outer    = <'credential-req-jwe', penc(inner, pkR_CI, ~rEnc)>
  in
    [ W_HasAT($Wid, $CI, $AS, ~sid, AT, ~skDPoP, pkDPoP),
      !CI_ReqEncPk($CI, pkR_CI),
      Fr(~skH), Fr(~iat), Fr(~jti_c), Fr(~skE_W), Fr(~rEnc), Fr(~skB) ]
  --[ Wallet_Sent_Cred_Req($Wid, $CI, ~sid, pkH, AT),
      Wallet_Sent_Cred_Req_Bind($Wid, $CI, ~sid, pkB),
      WalletGen_HolderKey($Wid, ~sid, pkH),
      WalletGen_EncKey($Wid, ~sid, pkE_W),
      WalletGen_BindKey($Wid, ~sid, pkB),
      HolderKeyFresh($Wid, ~skH, pkH),
      EncKeyFresh($Wid, ~skE_W, pkE_W) ]->
    [ W_AwaitingTxId_FIXED($Wid, $CI, $AS, ~sid, AT,
                           ~skH, pkH, ~skE_W, pkE_W, ~skB, pkB,
                           ~skDPoP, pkDPoP),
      !StoredHolderKey($Wid, ~skH, pkH),
      !StoredWalletEncKey($Wid, ~skE_W, pkE_W),
      !StoredBindKey($Wid, ~skB, pkB),
      Out(outer) ]
#endif

#ifdef FIXED_V2
rule Wallet_Send_Credential_Req [color=#d1fae5, role="Wallet"]:
  let
    pkH      = pk(~skH)
    pkE_W    = pk(~skE_W)
    pkB      = pk(~skB)
    keyProof = keyProofJWTV2($CI, pkH, pkB, ~iat, ~skH)
    dpopPC   = dpopProofCred($CI, pkDPoP, ~jti_c, AT, ~skDPoP)
    inner    = <'credential-req-v2', AT, dpopPC, pkH, keyProof,
                'crypt-resp', pkE_W, 'tid-bind', pkB>
    outer    = <'credential-req-jwe', penc(inner, pkR_CI, ~rEnc)>
  in
    [ W_HasAT($Wid, $CI, $AS, ~sid, AT, ~skDPoP, pkDPoP),
      !CI_ReqEncPk($CI, pkR_CI),
      Fr(~skH), Fr(~iat), Fr(~jti_c), Fr(~skE_W), Fr(~rEnc), Fr(~skB) ]
  --[ Wallet_Sent_Cred_Req($Wid, $CI, ~sid, pkH, AT),
      Wallet_Sent_Cred_Req_Bind($Wid, $CI, ~sid, pkB),
      WalletGen_HolderKey($Wid, ~sid, pkH),
      WalletGen_EncKey($Wid, ~sid, pkE_W),
      WalletGen_BindKey($Wid, ~sid, pkB),
      HolderKeyFresh($Wid, ~skH, pkH),
      EncKeyFresh($Wid, ~skE_W, pkE_W) ]->
    [ W_AwaitingTxId_FIXED($Wid, $CI, $AS, ~sid, AT,
                           ~skH, pkH, ~skE_W, pkE_W, ~skB, pkB,
                           ~skDPoP, pkDPoP),
      !StoredHolderKey($Wid, ~skH, pkH),
      !StoredWalletEncKey($Wid, ~skE_W, pkE_W),
      !StoredBindKey($Wid, ~skB, pkB),
      Out(outer) ]
#endif

// ★ V3: wallet uses the AT-bound holder keypair (~skH/pkH from W_HasAT_V3).
// No fresh ~skH here — pkH is fixed by the AT.
#ifdef FIXED_V3
rule Wallet_Send_Credential_Req [color=#d1fae5, role="Wallet"]:
  let
    pkE_W    = pk(~skE_W)
    pkB      = pk(~skB)
    keyProof = keyProofJWT($CI, pkH, ~iat, ~skH)        // pkH is AT-bound
    dpopPC   = dpopProofCred($CI, pkDPoP, ~jti_c, AT, ~skDPoP)
    inner    = <'credential-req-v3', AT, dpopPC, pkH, keyProof,
                'crypt-resp', pkE_W, 'tid-bind', pkB>
    outer    = <'credential-req-jwe', penc(inner, pkR_CI, ~rEnc)>
  in
    [ W_HasAT_V3($Wid, $CI, $AS, ~sid, AT,
                 ~skDPoP, pkDPoP, ~skH, pkH),
      !CI_ReqEncPk($CI, pkR_CI),
      Fr(~iat), Fr(~jti_c), Fr(~skE_W), Fr(~rEnc), Fr(~skB) ]
  --[ Wallet_Sent_Cred_Req($Wid, $CI, ~sid, pkH, AT),
      Wallet_Sent_Cred_Req_Bind($Wid, $CI, ~sid, pkB),
      WalletGen_EncKey($Wid, ~sid, pkE_W),
      WalletGen_BindKey($Wid, ~sid, pkB),
      EncKeyFresh($Wid, ~skE_W, pkE_W) ]->
    [ W_AwaitingTxId_V3($Wid, $CI, $AS, ~sid, AT,
                        ~skH, pkH, ~skE_W, pkE_W, ~skB, pkB,
                        ~skDPoP, pkDPoP),
      !StoredWalletEncKey($Wid, ~skE_W, pkE_W),
      !StoredBindKey($Wid, ~skB, pkB),
      Out(outer) ]
#endif


// ============================================================================
//   CREDENTIAL ENDPOINT — DEFERRED ISSUANCE
// ============================================================================

#ifdef VULNERABLE
rule CI_Credential_Endpoint_Defer [color=#fef9c3, role="CI"]:
  let
    keyProof    = keyProofJWT($CI, pkH, iat, skH_x)
    dpopPC      = dpopProofCred($CI, pkDPoP, jti_c, AT, skDPoP_x)
    inner       = <'credential-req', AT, dpopPC, pkH, keyProof,
                   'crypt-resp', pkE_W>
    outer       = <'credential-req-jwe', penc(inner, pk(~skR_CI), rEnc)>
    encResp_202 = penc(<'202-deferred', ~tid_ci>, pkE_W, ~rRespEnc)
  in
    [ In(outer),
      !CI_ReqEncSk($CI, ~skR_CI),
      !Valid_AT($CI, AT, $AS, $Wid_at, pkDPoP),
      !Ltk_CI($CI, ~ltkCI),
      Fr(~tid_ci), Fr(~rRespEnc) ]
  --[ _restrict( verify(keyProof, keyProofPayload($CI, pkH, iat),
                        pkH) = true ),
      _restrict( verify(dpopPC, dpopPayloadCred($CI, pkDPoP, jti_c, AT),
                        pkDPoP) = true ),
      OnlyOnceV(<'dpop-jti-cred', jti_c>),
      OnlyOnceV(<'tid-issued', ~tid_ci>),
      CI_Issued_TxId($CI, $AS, $Wid_at, ~tid_ci, AT, pkH, pkE_W, pkDPoP) ]->
    [ !CI_PendingTx_Vuln($CI, ~tid_ci, AT, $AS, $Wid_at, pkDPoP, pkH),
      !PendingTxId($Wid_at, $CI, ~tid_ci),
      Out(encResp_202) ]
#endif

